# Local Run Guide

## Option A: Start everything with one script (recommended)

```bash
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
./start-all.sh
```

This starts:
- Infrastructure (PostgreSQL + Kafka + Zookeeper)
- `auth-service` (8083)
- `loan-service` (8081)
- `notification-service` (8082)
- `api-gateway-service` (8080)
- `test-client` (8084)

Stop everything:

```bash
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
./stop-all.sh
```

## Option B: Start services individually

Terminal 1: Start infrastructure (PostgreSQL + Kafka + Zookeeper)

```
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
docker compose up
```

Terminal 2: Start auth-service (port 8083)

```
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
mvn -pl auth-service spring-boot:run
```

Terminal 3: Start loan-service (port 8081)

```
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
mvn -pl loan-service spring-boot:run
```

Terminal 4: Start notification-service (port 8082)

```
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
mvn -pl notification-service spring-boot:run
```

Terminal 5: Start api-gateway-service (port 8080)

```
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
mvn -pl api-gateway-service spring-boot:run
```

Terminal 6 (optional): Start test-client (port 8084)

```bash
cd /Users/shilpa/Documents/Projects/loan_origination
mvn -pl test-client spring-boot:run
```

Once running, test-client health endpoint:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8084/test/health
```

Then run smoke tests through:
- Gateway directly (`http://localhost:8080`)
- or test-client proxy endpoints (`http://localhost:8084/test/...`)

Postman collection: `docs/EP7-Gateway-Smoke-Test.postman_collection.json`.

Quick curl smoke tests:

```bash
./test-client-smoke.sh      # quick via test-client
./test-gateway.sh           # quick direct on gateway :8080
```

Full lifecycle (EP7-T4: all roles + transitions + DB/Kafka checks):

```bash
./test-client-lifecycle.sh  # via test-client -> gateway
./test-gateway-lifecycle.sh # direct on gateway :8080
```
